# Problem
How to install PowerCli on Windows

# Answer
Open PowerShell as Admin, run the command 
- Install-Module -Name VMware.PowerCLI -Scope CurrentUser -AllowClobber

# Reference
https://developer.vmware.com/powercli
https://blogs.vmware.com/PowerCLI/2017/04/powercli-install-process-powershell-gallery.html

# Steps

1. Right Click PowerShell 
2. Select "Run as Administrator"
3. Enter command
  Install-Module -Name VMware.PowerCLI -Scope CurrentUser -AllowClobber
4. Type Y at the prompt
  You'll see the Untrusted Repo warning
  May take a minute to run, so be patient
5. All Set
  At this point, you're all set, but you can make sure it was installed by running this command
  find-module -Name VMware.PowerCLI
